<DOC><DOCNO> AP881002-0072 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-02-88 2041EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-People-GreenArrest     10-02 0258</FIRST><SECOND>AM-People-Green Arrest,0264</SECOND><HEAD>Boxer Mitch Green Arrested Again; Drunken Driving Charged</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Boxer Mitch Green was arrested for the thirdtime in less than two weeks early Sunday and charged with drivingwhile impaired after police found him in a car that had crashedinto a parked vehicle, police said.   The accident caused no injuries and only minor damage, saidHousing Authority police Capt. Moe Leon. Green was alone and didnot resist arrest, but he refused to talk and police said theycould book him only after he was taken to a hospital to calm down.   Housing Authority police Sgt. Thomas Grippo said Green refusedto take a chemical breath test and began ``acting in a way where hewas going to hurt himself or others'' when he was first taken tocentral booking.   Two Housing Authority police officers found Green in a LincolnContinental that had crashed into an unoccupied parked car inQueens, said Leon.   Officers said Green's speech was slurred and they smelledalcohol on his breath, Leon said.   Green, 31, was arrested twice last month, on an assault chargepressed by a woman who has a child by Green, and on a disorderlyconduct charge.   On Aug. 23, Green and heavyweight champion Mike Tyson got into afight outside a boutique in Harlem. Green pressed assault charges,but dropped them three days later. He lost a bout with Tyson forthe U.S. Boxing Association heavyweight title in 1986.   Green's driver's license has been suspended 54 times, policehave said.</TEXT></DOC>